definition: Slovakia/Slovak/abbr. for 斯洛伐克[Si1 luo4 fa2 ke4]
prefecture/(old) province/(old) administrative division/state (e.g. of US)/oblast (Russia)/canton (Switzerland)

sentences.english: In Topeka , Kansas, it is illegal to drive ones car through a parade.
sentences.chinese: 在堪萨斯州的托皮卡，开车穿过游行队伍也是违法的。

sentences.english: Finally, he called the name of the senator from Kansas.
sentences.chinese: 最后，首席大法官叫到了这位堪萨斯州参议员的名字。

sentences.english: Much of Greensburg, Kansas has been leveled by a tornado.
sentences.chinese: 差不多整个堪萨斯州的格林斯堡都被龙卷风推平了。

sentences.english: And then moving to Topeka, Kansas.
sentences.chinese: 然后，移民到堪萨斯州的托贝卡。

sentences.english: She was not sure how it ended up in Kansas.
sentences.chinese: 但她也搞不清这封信为何最后跑到了堪萨斯州。

sentences.english: Final exams at Kansas University are only a few weeks away.
sentences.chinese: 堪萨斯州大学的期末考试刚刚过去几个星期。

sentences.english: Kansas is hardly a hotbed of eco-activism.
sentences.chinese: 堪萨斯州算不上生态主义的热土。

sentences.english: The postal abbreviation for Kansas is KS.
sentences.chinese: 堪萨斯州的邮政缩写是KS。

sentences.english: At Topeka , Kansas , he sketched the outline of a crop control measure .
sentences.chinese: 他在堪萨斯州的托皮卡勾画出农作物控制法的轮廓。

sentences.english: A city of east-central Kansas southwest of Topeka.
sentences.chinese: 美国堪萨斯州中东一城市，位于托皮卡西南。

sentences.english: Dwight Eisenhower came from a large family in Abilene, Kansas.
sentences.chinese: 艾森豪威尔来自一个大家族，在堪萨斯州阿比林。

sentences.english: The bones of Pteranodons have been found in Kansas in the United States and in England.
sentences.chinese: 在美国的堪萨斯州和英国发现过无齿翼龙的化石。

sentences.english: She is being held at the Fort Leavenworth military prison in Kansas.
sentences.chinese: 目前曼宁被关押在堪萨斯州利文沃斯堡军事监狱。

sentences.english: The smallest city was Wichita, Kansas. It had about three hundred sixty thousand people.
sentences.chinese: 最小的城市是堪萨斯州威奇托，人口约为36万。
